# SPACED - Backend (Supabase) MVP Checklist (v0.1)


— WEDGE ANCHOR —

Need a private place right now? Book a room near you in minutes.

Core moment:
Immediate need for discreet, short-duration private space.

————————————
Purpose

Define backend work needed in Supabase to support the MVP transaction loop.

---

Current status

- [ ] Supabase project wiring not yet implemented in app.
- [ ] No database schema or migration files in repo yet.
- [ ] No API layer for bookings/payments/access delivery yet.

---

Core Supabase build checklist

Auth and accounts

- [ ] Configure Supabase Auth project and environments.
- [ ] Implement email/password sign up and sign in.
- [ ] Add role model (guest, host, admin).
- [ ] Create user profile table linked to auth users.

Listings and availability

- [ ] Create `spaces` table (host, type, location, pricing, access type, status).
- [ ] Create `space_media` table (images).
- [ ] Create availability model (time slots or calendar windows).
- [ ] Enforce immediate availability queries ("available now").
- [ ] Add host listing create/update endpoints.

Bookings and session lifecycle

- [ ] Create `bookings` table with status lifecycle.
- [ ] Enforce MVP duration constraints (30/60 base, +15 increments).
- [ ] Enforce turnover buffer constraints (configurable 15-30 min).
- [ ] Add booking create endpoint with conflict checks.
- [ ] Add booking extension endpoint with conflict checks.
- [ ] Add booking confirmation payload for frontend.

Payments

- [ ] Define payment integration strategy (e.g., Stripe + webhook).
- [ ] Create `payments` table and payment event tracking.
- [ ] Implement checkout session creation endpoint.
- [ ] Implement payment webhook handling and booking status updates.

Access delivery

- [ ] Create `access_instructions` table/payload model.
- [ ] Support access types:
  - [ ] digital lock
  - [ ] lockbox
  - [ ] concierge/front desk
- [ ] Implement secure retrieval of access instructions only for confirmed bookings.

Security and policies

- [ ] Add Row Level Security (RLS) on all core tables.
- [ ] Add policies for guest/host access boundaries.
- [ ] Add audit fields (created_at, updated_at, created_by).
- [ ] Add basic abuse/rate-limit protections for booking endpoints.

Observability and ops

- [ ] Add structured logging for booking/payment/access flows.
- [ ] Add error monitoring and alerting for failed booking/payment events.
- [ ] Add seed data scripts for local development.

---

Definition of done (backend MVP)

- [ ] User can sign in.
- [ ] User can query available nearby spaces now.
- [ ] User can book 30/60 min and extend by 15 min when valid.
- [ ] Payment success confirms booking.
- [ ] User receives access instructions without host presence.
- [ ] Buffer rules prevent conflicting/too-tight consecutive bookings.
